    <!-- SECTION 4: ASHWAGANDHA FOR ANXIETY -->
    <h2>Ashwagandha for Anxiety: When to Expect Results</h2>

    <p>Anxiety reduction takes longer than general stress relief because anxiety involves deeper neurochemical patterns beyond cortisol alone. Ashwagandha modulates GABAergic signaling, serotonin pathways, and brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF) — changes that require sustained exposure to the active withanolides over multiple weeks. Clinical trials consistently show that significant anxiety improvement occurs at the 6-8 week mark.</p>

    <p>The Chandrasekhar 2012 study measured a 56.5% reduction in anxiety scores (Hamilton Anxiety Rating Scale) at 60 days with 600mg KSM-66 daily. A separate 2009 study by Cooley et al. compared ashwagandha to psychotherapy and found that 300mg twice daily for 12 weeks reduced anxiety (Beck Anxiety Inventory) significantly more than the psychotherapy control group. Both studies demonstrate that ashwagandha's anxiolytic effect is robust but requires patience.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="clock" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Weeks 1-2: Baseline Adjustment</h4>
        <p>No significant change in anxiety levels. The withanolides are accumulating in your system and beginning to modulate cortisol production. You may notice slightly improved sleep quality as an early sign.</p>
      </div>
