    <h2>Ashwagandha for Testosterone and Muscle: When to Expect Results</h2>

    <p>Testosterone and muscle gains represent ashwagandha's slowest-acting benefits — expect 8-12 weeks for meaningful results. The mechanism involves a cascade of hormonal changes: ashwagandha first lowers cortisol (which suppresses testosterone production), then increases DHEA-S (a testosterone precursor), and finally elevates free and total testosterone. This multi-step process simply takes more time than direct cortisol modulation.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">8-12 wks</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">is the clinical timeline for testosterone and muscle benefits. The Wankhede 2015 study showed a <strong>96.2 ng/dL increase in testosterone</strong> and significantly greater muscle strength gains after 8 weeks of 600mg KSM-66 combined with resistance training. Participants who took ashwagandha gained 3.5x more in bench press strength than placebo.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>The testosterone timeline explained</h3>

    <p>Cortisol and testosterone have an inverse relationship — when cortisol is chronically elevated, the body prioritizes stress hormone production at the expense of reproductive hormones. Ashwagandha's first action is lowering cortisol (weeks 2-4), which removes the hormonal "brake" on testosterone production. DHEA-S levels then begin to rise (weeks 4-6), followed by measurable increases in total and free testosterone (weeks 6-12).</p>

    <p>The Wankhede 2015 study provides the clearest data: 57 young men were randomized to 600mg KSM-66 or placebo while following a standardized resistance training program for 8 weeks. The ashwagandha group demonstrated:</p>

