      </table>
    </div>

    <p>These results are impressive but require two conditions: (1) a standardized KSM-66 extract at 600mg daily, and (2) a consistent resistance training program. Ashwagandha amplifies the effects of exercise — it does not replace it. For testosterone-focused product recommendations, see our guide to the <a href="/sports/best-testosterone-gummies/">best testosterone gummies</a>.</p>

    <!-- SECTION 7: WHY SOME PEOPLE DON'T FEEL IT -->
    <h2>Why Some People Don't Feel Ashwagandha Working</h2>

    <p>If you have taken ashwagandha for several weeks and feel nothing, do not assume it is a scam. There are five well-documented reasons why ashwagandha may not produce noticeable effects, and most of them are correctable.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="alert-circle" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>1. Dose Too Low</h4>
        <p>The clinical dose is 600mg of KSM-66 daily (typically split 300mg twice daily). Many commercial products contain only 150-300mg per serving, or use generic root powder instead of standardized extract. At sub-therapeutic doses, ashwagandha simply will not produce clinical-level effects. Check your label for both the total dose and the extract type.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="alert-triangle" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>2. Wrong Extract or Low-Quality Product</h4>
        <p>Generic ashwagandha root powder contains highly variable withanolide concentrations (0.5-10%). The clinical trials that established ashwagandha's benefits used standardized extracts — KSM-66 (5% withanolides) or Sensoril (10% withanolides). If your product does not specify the extract type, it may contain insufficient active compounds. Look for KSM-66 or Sensoril on the label.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="clock" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>3. Not Enough Time</h4>
        <p>This is the most common reason. Many people quit ashwagandha after 1-2 weeks because they "don't feel anything." Clinical studies ran for 8-12 weeks, and most benefits require a minimum of 4 weeks to manifest. The adaptogenic mechanism involves gradual recalibration of the HPA axis — this is not a process that happens overnight.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="coffee" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>4. Poor Absorption (Empty Stomach)</h4>
        <p>Ashwagandha's withanolides are fat-soluble compounds that require dietary fat for optimal absorption. Taking ashwagandha on an empty stomach significantly reduces bioavailability. Always take it with a meal or snack that contains healthy fats — avocado, nuts, olive oil, or eggs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="zap" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>5. Unrealistic Expectations</h4>
        <p>Ashwagandha is not a stimulant or a sedative — you will not "feel" it kick in the way you feel caffeine or melatonin. The effects are gradual and often noticed in retrospect: "I realize I haven't felt as anxious this month" or "I've been sleeping better without trying." If you are expecting a dramatic, acute sensation, you will be disappointed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="heart" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>6. Normal Cortisol Baseline</h4>
        <p>Ashwagandha is most effective in people with elevated cortisol and chronic stress. If your cortisol levels are already in the normal range, the adaptogenic effect will be less pronounced because there is less to correct. This does not mean ashwagandha is not working — it means your baseline is already healthy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>If you want to verify whether your ashwagandha supplement is actually delivering the claimed dose, look for products with third-party testing certificates (COA). Our guide to <a href="/blog/do-ashwagandha-gummies-work/">do ashwagandha gummies work</a> covers quality verification in detail and explains how to distinguish effective products from underdosed ones.</p>

    <!-- SECTION 8: HOW TO MAKE ASHWAGANDHA WORK FASTER -->
    <h2>How to Make Ashwagandha Work Faster</h2>

    <p>While you cannot bypass the biological timeline entirely, you can optimize absorption and create conditions that allow ashwagandha to reach its full potential as quickly as possible. These evidence-based strategies can shave days to weeks off the timeline compared to suboptimal supplementation practices.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="coffee" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Step 1: Take With Food (Especially Fats)</h4>
        <p>Withanolides are fat-soluble. A 2020 pharmacokinetic study showed that taking ashwagandha with a fat-containing meal increased blood levels of withanolides by approximately 20-30% compared to fasted administration. Pair your ashwagandha dose with breakfast or dinner that includes healthy fats.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="zap" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Step 2: Add Black Pepper (Piperine)</h4>
        <p>Piperine — the active compound in black pepper extract — inhibits hepatic and intestinal glucuronidation, which increases the bioavailability of many supplements including ashwagandha. Some products already include BioPerine. If yours does not, take 5-10mg of piperine alongside your ashwagandha dose.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="calendar" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Step 3: Be Consistent with Timing</h4>
        <p>Take ashwagandha at the same time every day. The HPA axis responds to consistent hormonal inputs — erratic dosing (skipping days, taking it at random times) reduces the steady-state withanolide levels needed for adaptive changes. Set a daily alarm or pair it with an existing habit (breakfast, dinner).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="award" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Step 4: Use the Right Dose (600mg KSM-66)</h4>
        <p>Do not underdose. The clinical trials that established the timelines in this article used 600mg of KSM-66 daily — typically 300mg morning and 300mg evening. Lower doses may still work, but they will likely take longer to produce results and the magnitude of effect will be smaller.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

